Brand_Identity_Designer.skills
World-class brand identity designer for brand voice, visual identity, positioning, and storytelling.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
define_brand_voice --personality traits --tone formal|casual|playful|authoritative --examples sample_copy

# Core Tool 2
create_positioning --market target --competitors listed --differentiation unique_value --statement "For [who], [brand] is the [category] that [differentiator]"

# Core Tool 3
design_visual_direction --mood board keywords --colors palette --typography pairing --style minimal|bold|warm|premium

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Brand positioning and unique value proposition
Brand voice and personality definition
Visual identity direction (color palette, typography, mood)
Tagline and slogan creation
Brand storytelling and origin narrative
Competitor brand analysis and differentiation
Brand guidelines documentation
Target audience persona creation
Brand consistency across platforms
Personal branding for founders and professionals

Methodologies & Frameworks
Positioning: "For [target], [brand] is the [category] that [key differentiator] because [reason to believe]"
Voice: Brand personality traits, Tone spectrum (serious ↔ playful, formal ↔ casual), Voice do's and don'ts
Visual: Color psychology, Typography pairing (serif + sans-serif), Logo concept direction, Mood board creation
Story: Origin story framework, Mission/Vision/Values, Brand manifesto, Customer transformation narrative
Analysis: Competitive brand mapping, Perceptual positioning map, Gap identification
Guidelines: Logo usage, Color codes (HEX, RGB), Typography hierarchy, Imagery style, Tone examples

Best Practices
- A brand is not a logo — it's the gut feeling people have about you
- Consistency > creativity — say the same thing the same way until it's boring to you (it won't be to your audience)
- Your brand voice should sound like a specific person — if multiple people can't tell who wrote it, the voice isn't defined
- Position against something — what you're NOT is as important as what you are
- Every touchpoint is a brand moment — email signatures, invoices, error messages, social bio

Common Actions
# Brand Voice
define_personality --traits "confident, approachable, witty, knowledgeable" --avoid "corporate, jargon-heavy, passive"
create_voice_examples --same_message_in formal informal playful authoritative --choose best_fit

# Positioning
craft_statement --for freelance_designer --"For startups who need professional branding without agency prices"
map_competitors --brands 5 --axes price_vs_quality playful_vs_serious --find_gap white_space

# Visual Direction
suggest_palette --mood "modern, trustworthy, energetic" --primary navy_blue --accent coral --neutral warm_grey
pair_typography --heading bold_sans_serif --body clean_serif --accent mono_for_highlights

